003e 231182b088172b9b309745748d539929edeab937\nzh-TW -\u003e 231182b088172b9b309745748d539929edeab937\n", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": "64fa2bb233460f282a3109903597b4df94670baa", "git_parents": ["00569b4393c515171e9335ce21199952e5a128ff"], "node": "b57d637dfa4186032314cd61fc220aaa0e7b59a3", "parents": ["4869bd83c04e6eed96f13647fc9178f81ff2c3b6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779267889, "git_changesets": ["00569b4393c515171e9335ce21199952e5a128ff", "64fa2bb233460f282a3109903597b4df94670baa"], "user": "ffxbld@lando.moz.tools"}, "26397": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040754 - Close SerialPort HANDLE synchronously in PlatformPipeReader::CloseWithStatus,  a=RyanVM\n\nThis aims to avoid issues with the current delayed closing of the handle by\nmaking us close the handle synchronously. This requires us to cancel I/O from a\ndifferent thread, so the cancellation logic has shifted to using CancelIoEx\ninstead of CancelIo on Windows.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301431\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301485\n", "files": ["xpcom/io/AsyncPlatformPipes.cpp"], "git_node": "d31b494b74993d4cb929bc4749bb57cde8f121e9", "git_parents": ["64fa2bb233460f282a3109903597b4df94670baa"], "node": "76979657d0090935492d61a08450dc5439a71ac2", "parents": ["b57d637dfa4186032314cd61fc220aaa0e7b59a3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779275297, "git_changesets": ["d31b494b74993d4cb929bc4749bb57cde8f121e9"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26398": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jan Grulich \u003cjgrulich@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040112 - WebRTC backport: Wayland capture: Fix integer overflow in cursor bitmap validation  a=RyanVM\n\nUse 64-bit arithmetic for the cursor bitmap bounds check to avoid\nincorrect results with large values.\n\nThis is a simple backport of an WebRTC upstream change.\n\nUpstrea