 "0f3c02a6619b1e47f67549b03a9d038c2824427c", "parents": ["16272f064bf1de0bef011ad6e0257504c3768d13"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779382550, "git_changesets": ["a25b601569b155a1a627830de9d61b257f715b83"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26430": {"changesets": [{"author": "bytesized \u003cbytesized@users.noreply.github.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040775 - Show the Send Tab context menus when the account requires verification  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301406\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301828\n", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-sync.js", "browser/base/content/test/sync/browser_contextmenu_sendpage.js", "browser/base/content/test/sync/browser_contextmenu_sendtab.js"], "git_node": "f8da2c00cd2a3fbabf579e56b03087babe3076c6", "git_parents": ["a25b601569b155a1a627830de9d61b257f715b83"], "node": "32b48e9c90c8c5c70e1595a861d4ad9b67894448", "parents": ["0f3c02a6619b1e47f67549b03a9d038c2824427c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779382587, "git_changesets": ["f8da2c00cd2a3fbabf579e56b03087babe3076c6"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26431": {"changesets": [{"author": "Stephen A Pohl \u003cspohl@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040809: Restore menu-bar Edit \u003e Undo and Edit \u003e Redo on macOS.  a=RyanVM\n\nBug 2036608 wired the standard Edit menu items in widget/cocoa/nsMenuItemX.mm\nto native NSResponder selectors (paste:, copy:, cut:, undo:, redo:, delete:,\nselectAll:) with target=nil, so AppKit propagates them via the macOS\nresponder chain. That works for cut:/copy:/paste:/delete:/selectAll: because\nNSResponder does not implement any of those by default; when no responder in\nthe chain claims the action, AppKit walks up to MacApplicationDelegate, whose\nforwarders (also added in bug 2036608) route each selector to\n[nsMenuBarX::sNativeEventTarget menuItemHit:] -- i.e. Gecko's command system.\n\nundo: and redo: are different. NSResponder ships with default implementations\nof those two methods (since macOS 10.7): each looks up the responder's\nundoManager property and forwards undo / redo to it. The default undoManager\nwalks the responder chain for an NSUndoManager and finds none, because Gecko\nmanages undo state via its own TransactionManager. The silent no-op that\nresults consumes the action before the AppDelegate forwarder is reached, so\nGecko's cmd_undo / cmd_redo never fires. End result: clicking Edit \u003e Undo or\nEdit \u003e Redo in the system menu bar does nothing in any Firefox window on\nmacOS.\n\nNarrowly revert menu_undo and menu_redo from NSResponder selectors back to\nmenuItemHit: dispatch. cut/copy/paste/delete/selectAll keep the\nresponder-chain wiring from bug 2036608. Net behaviour change vs.\npre-bug-2036608: none -- the accidental side-benefit that bug 2036608\nintroduced (Cmd+Z working inside native NSSavePanel sheets via the sheet\nfield editor's NSUndoManager) is given back. Keyboard Cmd+Z / Cmd+Shift+Z\ncontinue to work everywhere via Gecko's keyDown: interpretation.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301430\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301863\n", "files": ["widget/cocoa/nsMenuItemX.mm"], "git_node": "a1ea29cdf8c870cdc6118cfb2a942909692e4e37", "git_parents": ["f8da2c00cd2a3fbabf579e56b03087babe3076c6"], "node": "abdf5d814e99791d97af4c49abe18d4b2c1102f3", "parents": ["32b48e9c90c8c5c70e1595a861d4ad9b67894448"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779382624, "git_changesets": ["a1ea29cdf8c870cdc6118cfb2a942909692e4e37"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26432": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update remote-settings mobile-experiments ct-logs -  a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301903\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/raw/initial_experiments.json", "security/ct/CTKnownLogs.h", "security/manager/tools/log_list.json", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons-bloomfilters.json", "services/settings/dumps/main/newtab-wallpapers-v2.json"], "git_node": "084f0d59fd3b659fc5ead044d504dca545ae75a8", "git_parents": ["a1ea29cdf8c870cdc6118cfb2a942909692e4e37"], "node": "46a17f4929309fe6f189ad1d4b558f1a1b11fae0", "parents": ["abdf5d814e99791d97af4c49abe18d4b2c1102f3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779404781, "git_changesets": ["084f0d59fd3b659fc5ead044d504dca545ae75a8"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26433": {"changesets": [{"author": "Elissa Cha \u003cecha@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2036194 - Set up Glean metric for Smart Window user feedback  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D298410\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301922\n", "files": ["browser/components/asrouter/metrics.yaml"], "git_node": "0beb2b8978e8e1d536f96a6dc20f4a66828c867f", "git_parents": ["084f0d59fd3b659fc5ead044d504dca545ae75a8"], "node": "1e214e49f75b0c44a005ae2af954dfa415f522f0", "parents": ["46a17f4929309fe6f189ad1d4b558f1a1b11fae0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1779404826, "git_changesets": ["0beb2b8978e8e1d536f96a6dc20f4a66828c867f"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26434": {"changesets": [{"author": "Elissa Cha \u003cecha@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2039097 - Support width and height params for OPEN_URL chromeless windows  a=RyanVM\n\n- Adds optional `width` / `height` support for chromeless windows opened via `OPEN_URL`\n- Threads the params through `SpecialMessageActions` into `URILoadingHelper`\n- Intended to be used for \"Learn more\" link in Smart Window User Feedback modal\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D300478\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301920\n", "files": ["browser/modules/URILoadingHelper.sys.mjs", "browser/modules/test/browser/browser_URILoading