8cd95e2e89"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780505871, "git_changesets": ["ce53ccae1769e0c74a08f8243d290e3883e8373b"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26701": {"changesets": [{"author": "Yury Delendik \u003cydelendik@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2042767 - Skip non-debug wasm frames in wasmUpdateBytecodeOffset.  a=RyanVM\n\nWith JSPI active, a JitActivation can contain wasm frames belonging to the\nbuiltin module (compiled with DebugEnabled::False). The search loop in\nwasmUpdateBytecodeOffset was calling debugFrame() on every wasm frame it\nencountered, but DebugFrame::from() asserts debugEnabled(). Guard the call\nwith debugEnabled() so non-debug frames are skipped.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303168\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304436\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/js-promise-integration/debug-frame-offset-non-debug.js", "js/src/vm/FrameIter.cpp"], "git_node": "9ee7a00e565a98949429ff466b92a825720bf363", "git_parents": ["ce53ccae1769e0c74a08f8243d290e3883e8373b"], "node": "9d64b004f4b398c11b3a9c8040b70df88f0e187e", "parents": ["f27a26baec91a454a72ecd43c15a883c4a2d37eb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780505898, "git_changesets": ["9ee7a00e565a98949429ff466b92a825720bf363"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26702": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003crvandermeulen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2039791 - Bump Application Services to version 152.0.1. a=RyanVM\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/plugins/dependencies/src/main/java/ApplicationServices.kt"], "git_node": "333328328b171f3583c744fc1be9375d0fae1efc", "git_parents": ["9ee7a00e565a98949429ff466b92a825720bf363"], "node": "bd268cfea9585e16f8f272f417b0de15c5d355c4", "parents": ["9d64b004f4b398c11b3a9c8040b70df88f0e187e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780516482, "git_changesets": ["333328328b171f3583c744fc1be9375d0fae1efc"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26703": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003crvandermeulen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Revert \"Bug 1201160 - Skip ServiceWorker interception for no_cors subresource fetching from CSS. r=asuth,dom-worker-reviewers\" for causing bug 2029029.\n\nThis reverts commit 596b0965fb77838dd1c2dca15caea844e9cd6565.\n", "files": ["dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerInterceptController.cpp"], "git_node": "eb884ec2edab6f4dfe2c4a802606c6cd01850e4b", "git_parents": ["333328328b171f3583c744fc1be9375d0fae1efc"], "node": "38e1362ea6079998ed1dae19375ed5ff734fc59f", "parents": ["bd268cfea9585e16f8f272f417b0de15c5d355c4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780516822, "git_changesets": ["eb884ec2edab6f4dfe2c4a802606c6cd01850e4b"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26704": {"changesets": [{"author": "Duncan McIntosh \u003cdmcintosh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2042913 - Always look for the desktop launcher in the user's profile when computing telemetry.  a=RyanVM\n\n$DESKTOP is relative to the current shell variable context. Originally,\nthe stub installer telemetry set the shell variable context to current\n(see [0]), but this wasn't transferred over to the telemetry.nsh\nversion. More precisely, the following metrics used the 'current'\ncontext:\n\n  * new_default / old_default\n    These were always computed relative to HKCU/HKLM explicitly, so they\n    didn't actually vary with the shell var context.\n\n  * launched_by, had_old_install, set_default\n    These don't depend on the shell var context either (they examined\n    command line arguments and globals for the first two, set_default\n    was just hardcoded.)\n\n  * desktop_launcher_status\n    This DID depend on the shell variable context, so it broke when it\n    was switched over to telemetry.nsh in bug 2020016, since the shell\n    var context change was overlooked.\n\nWhen checking the status, it would look in 'C:\\Users\\Public\\Desktop',\nnotice that it didn't exist since we installed it in the user's profile,\nthen it would incorrectly report that it had to have been removed.\n\nIdeally, this would use $USERDESKTOP, but that isn't available in the\nversion of NSIS we're currently using (which is a shame, ideally this\ncode wouldn't touch ShellVarContext at all). Instead, switch the shell\nvar context for the call, and switch it back after.\n\nThanks to :aborondo for calling out the unexpected metrics and for doing\nthe historical analysis (namely, that the context _was_ explicitly set\nprior to bug 2020016, not accidentally).\n\n[0]: https://github.com/mozilla-firefox/firefox/blob/1d806518bac92b273dabd1ea22c938e1b2143f35/browser/installer/windows/nsis/stub.nsh#L903\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302884\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304437\n", "files": ["browser/installer/windows/nsis/telemetry.nsh"], "git_node": "d3d5df11bd6887b2b20d9d6cc5f217f60ea57d8c", "git_parents": ["eb884ec2edab6f4dfe2c4a802606c6cd01850e4b"], "node": "826bdbd6395e6e4057209ec8395e11dbbd468fc4", "parents": ["38e1362ea6079998ed1dae19375ed5ff734fc59f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517457, "git_changesets": ["d3d5df11bd6887b2b20d9d6cc5f217f60ea57d8c"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26705": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andreas Farre \u003cfarre@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2039866 - FindAdjacentEntryFor should never return its input.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302724\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304453\n", "files": ["docshell/shistory/nsSHistory.cpp"], "git_node": "cd39d47ad98790d0240be7a117d6f4071d4a4665", "git_parents": ["d3d5df11bd6887b2b20d9d6cc5f217f60ea57d8c"], "node": "15a27cfcbbe1d09ec6212d529ec043971d497e6a", "parents": ["826bdbd6395e6e4057209ec8395e11dbbd468fc4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517494, "git_changesets": ["cd39d47ad98790d0240be7a117d6f4071d4a4665"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26706": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2043780 - Remove the Nimbus flag and existing preference keys for Settings.enableHomepageSearchBar  a=RyanVM\n\n- It appears that users might still have the HomepageSearchBar setting enabled after the experiment has ended or have manually enabled the secret settings after we have removed rendering the Homepage Search Bar in Bug 2034877.\n- To combat this, we are removing the Nimbus flag. Future experiments should use a new Nimbus flag to be safe.\n- We changed the preference key for the underlying Settings.enableHomepageSearchBar to ensure it is always false.\n- Removes the Homepage Search Bar from secret settings to prevent accidental usages.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303642\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304506\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/nimbus.fml.yaml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/settings/SecretSettingsFragment.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/utils/Settings.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values/preference_keys.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/values/static_strings.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/xml/secret_settings_preferences.xml"], "git_node": "b9b0be2aeecd8af47c7ada404b3b6423c2c15ee5", "git_parents": ["cd39d47ad98790d0240be7a117d6f4071d4a4665"], "node": "0553c5929df6aed39f16d7d5e1cb135a0d80f296", "parents": ["15a27cfcbbe1d09ec6212d529ec043971d497e6a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517519, "git_changesets": ["b9b0be2aeecd8af47c7ada404b3b6423c2c15ee5"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26707": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041693 - Part 1: Tint mozac_ic_* icons in XML with ?attr/colorOnSurface  a=RyanVM\n\n- Performed a search for mozac_ic_* icons in XML and added app:tint=\"?attr/colorOnSurface\" to ensure they will work on private theme\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303985\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304514\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/exception_item.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/fragment_pwa_onboarding.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/fragment_sign_out.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/layout_add_credit_card.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/library_site_item.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/overlay_add_on_progress.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/preference_widget_radiobutton_with_info.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/recently_closed_nav_item.xml", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/res/layout/search_engine_radio_button.xml"], "git_node": "5641de5de4698580b3064eac2c84aeaec53ec66e", "git_parents": ["b9b0be2aeecd8af47c7ada404b3b6423c2c15ee5"], "node": "2ad35a7b84f356cd0c61fcf0ceaa266264098c74", "parents": ["0553c5929df6aed39f16d7d5e1cb135a0d80f296"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041693 - Part 2: Tint the history group and recently closed list icon with ?attr/colorOnSurface  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303986\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304515\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/library/history/viewholders/HistoryListItemViewHolder.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/library/recentlyclosed/RecentlyClosedFragmentView.kt"], "git_node": "2eb1b296de2958bdf7075ca61bc010df57e3b265", "git_parents": ["5641de5de4698580b3064eac2c84aeaec53ec66e"], "node": "20abd0ce0e10aaa1e113e3a6c8df3cebb19cbe1a", "parents": ["2ad35a7b84f356cd0c61fcf0ceaa266264098c74"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517578, "git_changesets": ["5641de5de4698580b3064eac2c84aeaec53ec66e", "2eb1b296de2958bdf7075ca61bc010df57e3b265"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26708": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rebecca King \u003crking@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2044432 - Add a Nimbus variable to set the IPP upgradeNotAvailable pref -  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304182\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304462\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/nimbus/FeatureManifest.yaml"], "git_node": "c47cc1875a1bdda2e886713a9a158d4e4ca3dc10", "git_parents": ["2eb1b296de2958bdf7075ca61bc010df57e3b265"], "node": "f4e4a48e79a0d1c987efdeb96d962e7ca9f78f78", "parents": ["20abd0ce0e10aaa1e113e3a6c8df3cebb19cbe1a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517604, "git_changesets": ["c47cc1875a1bdda2e886713a9a158d4e4ca3dc10"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26709": {"changesets": [{"author": "Aaron Train \u003caaron.train@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2044530 - Swap out Pixel 10 for Galaxy S26+ on Robo-ARM  a=RyanVM DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304319\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304409\n", "files": ["mobile/android/test_infra/flank-configs/fenix/arm-robo-test.yml"], "git_node": "0816a8572a8ebf479bbd20ddfb451f7ecf959737", "git_parents": ["c47cc1875a1bdda2e886713a9a158d4e4ca3dc10"], "node": "2da2e07579e5fc5a0d2bd58764f5a82ff7ab904c", "parents": ["f4e4a48e79a0d1c987efdeb96d962e7ca9f78f78"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517794, "git_changesets": ["0816a8572a8ebf479bbd20ddfb451f7ecf959737"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26710": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ashley Hale \u003cahale@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033762 - Detect unsupported VideoProcessorBlt features at startup  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D295523\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304350\n", "files": ["dom/ipc/DOMTypes.ipdlh", "gfx/ipc/GraphicsMessages.ipdlh", "gfx/src/nsDeviceContext.cpp", "gfx/src/nsDeviceContext.h", "gfx/thebes/D3D11Checks.cpp", "gfx/thebes/D3D11Checks.h", "gfx/thebes/DeviceManagerDx.cpp", "gfx/thebes/DeviceManagerDx.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp", "layout/style/nsMediaFeatures.cpp", "widget/Screen.cpp", "widget/Screen.h", "widget/ScreenManager.cpp", "widget/android/ScreenHelperAndroid.cpp", "widget/cocoa/ScreenHelperCocoa.mm", "widget/gtk/ScreenHelperGTK.cpp", "widget/headless/HeadlessScreenHelper.cpp", "widget/uikit/ScreenHelperUIKit.mm", "widget/windows/ScreenHelperWin.cpp"], "git_node": "a39c2eec8cb5ab4ba3ad840d901ffad272b29627", "git_parents": ["0816a8572a8ebf479bbd20ddfb451f7ecf959737"], "node": "0eaa733705cbda472fd170a47d166fc270f618fb", "parents": ["2da2e07579e5fc5a0d2bd58764f5a82ff7ab904c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ashley Hale \u003cahale@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2042678 - Change VIDEO_HDR allowlist to blocklist with no entries  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302864\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304351\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp", "widget/GfxInfoFeatureDefs.inc", "widget/cocoa/GfxInfo.mm", "widget/gtk/GfxInfo.cpp", "widget/windows/GfxInfo.cpp"], "git_node": "15b47673bb8d08256ac0c679b5e093ce821938e0", "git_parents": ["a39c2eec8cb5ab4ba3ad840d901ffad272b29627"], "node": "6ba3c898cb4902af5c6035e3b96d0d4611793ecf", "parents": ["0eaa733705cbda472fd170a47d166fc270f618fb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780517885, "git_changesets": ["a39c2eec8cb5ab4ba3ad840d901ffad272b29627", "15b47673bb8d08256ac0c679b5e093ce821938e0"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26711": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041373.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301919\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302418\n", "files": ["dom/media/platforms/ffmpeg/FFmpegVideoDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/ffmpeg/FFmpegVideoDecoder.h"], "git_node": "fbfcb9095bd3934a78d10119919431cf4f18b013", "git_parents": ["15b47673bb8d08256ac0c679b5e093ce821938e0"], "node": "610f8982e8b0dad451233f3a27dcd22101086112", "parents": ["6ba3c898cb4902af5c6035e3b96d0d4611793ecf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780525724, "git_changesets": ["fbfcb9095bd3934a78d10119919431cf4f18b013"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26712": {"changesets": [{"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 1: do not autosize the report broken panel, just do what we did before the redesign;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302067\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304466\n", "files": ["browser/components/reportbrokensite/test/browser/head.js", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI-shared.css"], "git_node": "5eb60dca72ea3e0d9906ee373dc5c086bf0eda16", "git_parents": ["fbfcb9095bd3934a78d10119919431cf4f18b013"], "node": "53f4eb81b27d62a526da53dfda52b49cfc1f27f7", "parents": ["610f8982e8b0dad451233f3a27dcd22101086112"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 2: ignore the next mouse move after we deliberately focus on an invalid input;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302068\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304467\n", "files": ["browser/components/reportbrokensite/ReportBrokenSite.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "84b94582e3698c853d2d8e339b2a3c52fecbbfd0", "git_parents": ["5eb60dca72ea3e0d9906ee373dc5c086bf0eda16"], "node": "9a51cddbddb8772d92303faabe213eeeb2a60b02", "parents": ["53f4eb81b27d62a526da53dfda52b49cfc1f27f7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 3: remove no-longer-wanted code to randomize the reason selector options on Report Broken Site, and re-order the default choices a little;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302069\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304468\n", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/reportbrokensite/ReportBrokenSite.sys.mjs", "browser/components/reportbrokensite/content/reportBrokenSitePanel.inc.xhtml", "browser/components/reportbrokensite/test/browser/browser.toml", "browser/components/reportbrokensite/test/browser/browser_reason_randomization.js"], "git_node": "7668eb927d6295673d694c1d5b70c91676256e34", "git_parents": ["84b94582e3698c853d2d8e339b2a3c52fecbbfd0"], "node": "07301a0bb9edd49233d0137ededdb83f4a02fe90", "parents": ["9a51cddbddb8772d92303faabe213eeeb2a60b02"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 4: use a better tooltip text than 'invalid' for the Report Broken Site comment box;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302070\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304469\n", "files": ["browser/components/reportbrokensite/ReportBrokenSite.sys.mjs"], "git_node": "24685772bb684325be399fa794f2aaef0c5d360e", "git_parents": ["7668eb927d6295673d694c1d5b70c91676256e34"], "node": "1fe70aded84d82c6f2ac942cb0089c8c51055489", "parents": ["07301a0bb9edd49233d0137ededdb83f4a02fe90"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 5: add more space between send-more-info and report-preview on the Report Broken Site details view, and hide their superfluous border on Nova;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302071\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304470\n", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI-shared.css"], "git_node": "ded313a58f6811cfefd78114c1c9143f4436bec3", "git_parents": ["24685772bb684325be399fa794f2aaef0c5d360e"], "node": "756d4ee987f1258f5d775abff526d6c4179258be", "parents": ["1fe70aded84d82c6f2ac942cb0089c8c51055489"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 6: add a label above each URL input on Report Broken Site;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302072\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304471\n", "files": ["browser/components/reportbrokensite/content/reportBrokenSitePanel.inc.xhtml", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/reportBrokenSite.ftl", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI-shared.css"], "git_node": "cc4331d7309ca00e300bd91631d7413170c1a9a2", "git_parents": ["ded313a58f6811cfefd78114c1c9143f4436bec3"], "node": "9ae8183e3bdb5df62a89d6880239afb79467823d", "parents": ["756d4ee987f1258f5d775abff526d6c4179258be"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 7: fix progression-disabling while changing the URLs on Report Broken Site;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302073\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304472\n", "files": ["browser/components/reportbrokensite/ReportBrokenSite.sys.mjs", "browser/components/reportbrokensite/test/browser/browser_url_widgets.js"], "git_node": "c8e295102c7168ab6e016d3d5825ce69cd3df4cd", "git_parents": ["cc4331d7309ca00e300bd91631d7413170c1a9a2"], "node": "1e72ae4317168149491f0f118c4ffcc87122bac8", "parents": ["9ae8183e3bdb5df62a89d6880239afb79467823d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040437 - part 8: improve tab-key handling on panels to account for the activeElement being in a shadowRoot so tree-walking doesn't begin with the first navigable element;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302074\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304473\n", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/PanelMultiView.sys.mjs", "browser/components/customizableui/test/browser_PanelMultiView_keyboard.js"], "git_node": "44813dcc43370cdc432c055761a4300a21d99c20", "git_parents": ["c8e295102c7168ab6e016d3d5825ce69cd3df4cd"], "node": "a2e8eba1013bd979977a53a525195078dd1ee5f2", "parents": ["1e72ae4317168149491f0f118c4ffcc87122bac8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2006121 - allow keyboard-focus to fall on Report Broken Site preview data so screen-readers may read the text;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302211\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304474\n", "files": ["browser/components/reportbrokensite/ReportBrokenSite.sys.mjs", "browser/components/reportbrokensite/test/browser/browser_tab_key_order.js", "browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI-shared.css"], "git_node": "c4ef1b8d5a32b6c4709425a5f40b6a0b39cab997", "git_parents": ["44813dcc43370cdc432c055761a4300a21d99c20"], "node": "2bcade133110268cc224ecd298da7acaba5aba67", "parents": ["a2e8eba1013bd979977a53a525195078dd1ee5f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003ctwisniewski@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2006157, 2006161 - improve HCM styling for Report Broken Site;  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302212\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304475\n", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI-shared.css"], "git_node": "fb6fc1eda273a52cbf347e82b770e02484659fce", "git_parents": ["c4ef1b8d5a32b6c4709425a5f40b6a0b39cab997"], "node": "671b718838b0af51151cf65d4895b083b57361e8", "parents": ["2bcade133110268cc224ecd298da7acaba5aba67"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780525982, "git_changesets": ["5eb60dca72ea3e0d9906ee373dc5c086bf0eda16", "84b94582e3698c853d2d8e339b2a3c52fecbbfd0", "7668eb927d6295673d694c1d5b70c91676256e34", "24685772bb684325be399fa794f2aaef0c5d360e", "ded313a58f6811cfefd78114c1c9143f4436bec3", "cc4331d7309ca00e300bd91631d7413170c1a9a2", "c8e295102c7168ab6e016d3d5825ce69cd3df4cd", "44813dcc43370cdc432c055761a4300a21d99c20", "c4ef1b8d5a32b6c4709425a5f40b6a0b39cab997", "fb6fc1eda273a52cbf347e82b770e02484659fce"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26713": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tim Giles \u003ctgiles@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2037667 - Part 1: Restructure preferences test manifests for SRD pref flip  a=RyanVM\n\nAdd `dupe-manifest = true` to browser-srd.toml so shared tests can run\nwithout build system errors.\n\nMove the audited set of shared tests into browser-srd.toml so they run\nwith `browser.settings-redesign.enabled=true`. Remove\nbrowser_advanced_update.js from browser-srd.toml since it only covers\nthe legacy General pane.\n\nSplit browser_accessibility_pane.js, browser_appearance_pane, and\nbrowser_colors_dialog into `_xul.js` copies that retain the\nlegacy/XUL-only assertions. This ensures we don't lose the pane-specific\ncoverage when the SRD pref is disabled, while allowing the non `_xul.js`\nfiles to handle the SRD related changes in the next commit in this\nstack.\n\nAdd an `openPrefsTab` helper to head.js for tests that need to open the\npreferences UI at a specific category and wait for `paneshown`. This\nreplaces the `openPreferencesViaOpenPreferencesAPI` and similar observer\nsetups across the test directory.\n\nNote: this part depends on the next commit in the stack (Part 2) for any\nshared test referenced from browser-srd.toml to function under the\nenabled redesign pref. They must land or back out together.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302555\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304456\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/browser-srd.toml", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser.toml", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_accessibility_pane_xul.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_appearance_pane_xul.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_colors_dialog_xul.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/head.js"], "git_node": "0cc44bfcb4f3608c3d709c6e41e46d916100ce91", "git_parents": ["fb6fc1eda273a52cbf347e82b770e02484659fce"], "node": "ebb70ccb11ddddd9647a40ba8d0413e1928a8ad3", "parents": ["671b718838b0af51151cf65d4895b083b57361e8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Giles \u003ctgiles@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2037667 - Part 2: Update shared preferences tests for SRD pref flip  a=RyanVM\n\nUpdate shared preferences tests so they pass under both the legacy XUL\npreferences and the new settings redesign preferences. Each file follows\none or more of these patterns:\n\n- Calls `openPrefsTab` helper from head.js for pane navigation.\n- Replace hard-coded pane/subcategory selectors with unscoped versions.\n  SRD pane containers don't have a DOM id while the legacy containers\n  do.\n- Add SRD-conditional branches for elements that change when the\n  redesign is enabled. This includes pane location, DOM shape, or\n  telemetry bucket changes.\n- Guard null-element accesses, fix sync-pane-loaded observer leaks, and\n  use assertions with a tolerance value where exact equality checks were\n  too strict.\n- Drop redundant inline `browser.settings-redesign.enabled=true`\n  pushPrefEnv calls.\n\nNote: This commit pairs with the previous commit in the stack (Part 1).\nbrowser-srd.toml entries added there reference these files, so these two\ncommits must land or back out together.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302556\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304457\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_accessibility_pane.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_appearance_pane.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_bug1018066_resetScrollPosition.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_bug1020245_openPreferences_to_paneContent.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_build_font_options_test.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_checkspelling.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_colors_dialog.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_fluent.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_privacy_trustPanelBreachAlerts.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_tabs_open_external_next_to_active_tab.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_updates_managed_by_os.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_windows_launch_on_login.js"], "git_node": "2543305217a497badedf9a289ff78a4b7f414d54", "git_parents": ["0cc44bfcb4f3608c3d709c6e41e46d916100ce91"], "node": "a5afca5fa2b4c8c06c946e9465cfa906fb0fde16", "parents": ["ebb70ccb11ddddd9647a40ba8d0413e1928a8ad3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Giles \u003ctgiles@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2037667 - Part 3: Add SRD coverage-gap regression tests  a=RyanVM\n\nAdd an SRD-only test that closes a new coverage gap discovered while\nmaking the shared tests pass when SRD is enabled.\n\n`browser_srd_telemetry_bucket_migration.js` ensures that when a setting\nmoves to a new pane, the recorded telemetry from Glean's\n`browserUiInteraction` is placed in the correct bucket. For example,\n`useSmoothScrolling` moved from General to Accessibility and so its\ninteraction should be recorded in Accessibility.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302557\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304458\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/browser-srd.toml", "browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_srd_telemetry_bucket_migration.js"], "git_node": "0c6e938b4ae7437c2ac9c4e4e291bd8524cb5674", "git_parents": ["2543305217a497badedf9a289ff78a4b7f414d54"], "node": "861fc08a7f61f1c474d1c0ff693b4abb705bd55a", "parents": ["a5afca5fa2b4c8c06c946e9465cfa906fb0fde16"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Anna Kulyk \u003cakulyk@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2037667 - Part 4: Update browser_windows_launch_on_login_msix.js test  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303259\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304459\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/browser_windows_launch_on_login_msix.js"], "git_node": "8f039a9138f1327eaa8527e4d055a074f8c477bd", "git_parents": ["0c6e938b4ae7437c2ac9c4e4e291bd8524cb5674"], "node": "8a6b4abd561df6497f4ab46de0eb61535d871b8e", "parents": ["861fc08a7f61f1c474d1c0ff693b4abb705bd55a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Giles \u003ctgiles@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2043893 - Redirect langpacks URL to local server in browser-srd.toml tests.  a=RyanVM\n\nThis is the same issue as Bug 2041391, where langpacks are only loaded\nin non-Nightly builds and so the issue was not caught in the regressing\nbug, Bug 2037667. This is because of the\n`intl.multilingual.downloadEnabled` pref being set to \"true\" in\n`RELEASE_OR_BETA` and not DevEdition builds, see `firefox.js` for more\ndetails.\n\nBecause of the SRD related changes, the languages pane will eagerly\nfetch remote langpacks as soon as the pane becomes active. This fetch is\ngated on `intl.multilingual.downloadEnabled`, so the test always passes\non Nightly since the pref is always false on Nightly.\n\nAs for why this was not an issue before SRD, the remote langpacks fetch\nwould only occur when the `browserLanguages.js` dialog was opened, not\nwhen the pane itself was loaded. `browser_checkspelling.js` never opens\nthe Browser Languages dialog, so this was never an issue with the legacy\nsettings setup.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304194\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304460\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/browser-srd.toml"], "git_node": "004c3742cc64f1ede2f491e372fb1719b754639b", "git_parents": ["8f039a9138f1327eaa8527e4d055a074f8c477bd"], "node": "d09efde447ef374236faefa7f63c491570f9886a", "parents": ["8a6b4abd561df6497f4ab46de0eb61535d871b8e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780527440, "git_changesets": ["0cc44bfcb4f3608c3d709c6e41e46d916100ce91", "2543305217a497badedf9a289ff78a4b7f414d54", "0c6e938b4ae7437c2ac9c4e4e291bd8524cb5674", "8f039a9138f1327eaa8527e4d055a074f8c477bd", "004c3742cc64f1ede2f491e372fb1719b754639b"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26714": {"changesets": [{"author": "Anna Kulyk \u003cakulyk@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041441 - Part 1: Fix unlabeled inputs in Turn on backup and Connection settings dialogs  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303918\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304483\n", "files": ["browser/components/backup/content/turn-on-scheduled-backups.mjs", "browser/components/backup/tests/browser/browser_settings_turn_on_scheduled_backups.js", "browser/components/preferences/dialogs/connection.xhtml"], "git_node": "477e5f5ea394c8e38f74722908676a06bd99481f", "git_parents": ["004c3742cc64f1ede2f491e372fb1719b754639b"], "node": "7823835ee1875050cc3bf45867ec7f0033e22edf", "parents": ["d09efde447ef374236faefa7f63c491570f9886a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Anna Kulyk \u003cakulyk@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041441 - Part 2: Fix unlabeled inputs on Home and startup settings page  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303928\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304484\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser_homepage_firefox_home_recent_activity.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser_homepage_firefox_home_shortcuts.js", "browser/extensions/newtab/lib/AboutPreferences.sys.mjs", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/preferences/preferences.ftl", "python/l10n/fluent_migrations/bug_2041441_home_prefs_select_aria_labels.py"], "git_node": "bc19f56b7ef0a0c04c8a663b36c601c7ddeafdd9", "git_parents": ["477e5f5ea394c8e38f74722908676a06bd99481f"], "node": "722591e8dc9f1f9965a558160f787e28ae2886b1", "parents": ["7823835ee1875050cc3bf45867ec7f0033e22edf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780527470, "git_changesets": ["477e5f5ea394c8e38f74722908676a06bd99481f", "bc19f56b7ef0a0c04c8a663b36c601c7ddeafdd9"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26715": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nina Pypchenko \u003cnpypchenko@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2044507 - Add new toggle to remove logo/wordmark  a=RyanVM\n\nAdds a \"Firefox logo\" toggle to the Firefox Home section in about:preferences#home,\nletting users hide the logo on New Tab.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304314\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304362\n", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser-srd.toml", "browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser_homepage_firefox_home_disabled_both_off.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser_homepage_firefox_home_disabled_tabs_on.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser_homepage_firefox_home_disabled_windows_on.js", "browser/components/preferences/tests/home/browser_homepage_firefox_home_firefox_logo.js", "browser/extensions/newtab/lib/AboutPreferences.sys.mjs", "browser/extensions/newtab/test/unit/lib/AboutPreferences.test.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/preferences/preferences.ftl", "pyth