Original Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301322\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304604\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPPProxyManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProxyManager.js"], "git_node": "c020b0cc739c2ab17790bf377b78e557b39f4f06", "git_parents": ["426874ec64a468ba91b6b2c033e26b9baf112c2f"], "node": "dcbfeb09161499a49fae138d9cd6ed3100a4fa74", "parents": ["cce3ed4dcce8e4db4f094333874e7403d4d9d758"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040063 - Add limitedBandwidth field to the IPP Entitlement schema  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301664\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304605\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/GuardianTypes.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_GuardianClient.js"], "git_node": "e125f5631e0cfb8af402d13c5bc5007ca5de7a8a", "git_parents": ["c020b0cc739c2ab17790bf377b78e557b39f4f06"], "node": "a9f19d6bce2c00286618fc87a9577bc376dd6f2a", "parents": ["dcbfeb09161499a49fae138d9cd6ed3100a4fa74"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040065 - Update the IPP bandwidth enabled pref to be set by entitlement.limitedBandwidth  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302674\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304606\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/docs/Preferences.rst", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/fxa/IPPFxaBaseAuthProvider.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionService.js"], "git_node": "16243646bb08ab11a404ac58a4cad358107c489a", "git_parents": ["e125f5631e0cfb8af402d13c5bc5007ca5de7a8a"], "node": "5b2fe52428ba466fc395e08bcd54b736068f4a6a", "parents": ["a9f19d6bce2c00286618fc87a9577bc376dd6f2a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040512 - Guard IPProtectionPanel UsageChanged handler when bandwidth tracking is disabled  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302879\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304607\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionPanel.js"], "git_node": "614c6611898ab000478fed9ba40836cf1d783dce", "git_parents": ["16243646bb08ab11a404ac58a4cad358107c489a"], "node": "1240f935651ce9a5c111a4e8cae7ebd9917551f2", "parents": ["5b2fe52428ba466fc395e08bcd54b736068f4a6a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040511 - Return early in IPPUsageHelper and IPProtectionInfobarManager when bandwidth tracking is disabled  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302880\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304608\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/IPPUsageHelper.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionInfobarManager.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_IPPUsageHelper.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_ipprotection_infobar.js"], "git_node": "e95cf403c16884d92f1decdeb65b6bbc342c7b8c", "git_parents": ["614c6611898ab000478fed9ba40836cf1d783dce"], "node": "ef00bf203591c6ccc9b34c9f7fbfabfb843f804f", "parents": ["1240f935651ce9a5c111a4e8cae7ebd9917551f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2043020 - Part 1: Add unlimited to ProxyUsage  a=RyanVM\n\n- Adds an `unlimited` field to ProxyUsage, set from the\n`X-Quota-Unlimited` response header.\n- Dispatches a usage changed event when usage becomes unlimited.\n- Skips pause checks when usage is unlimited.\n- Saves unlimited in the IPPStartupCache.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303267\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304610\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/GuardianTypes.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPPProxyManager.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/IPPStartupCache.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_GuardianClient.js", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPPStartupCache.js", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProxyManager.js"], "git_node": "61db97a6d6bcd82aa210f8f865838f6d2d7aad88", "git_parents": ["e95cf403c16884d92f1decdeb65b6bbc342c7b8c"], "node": "3f96763e07e336cff841f48f69e9b98b0614f95e", "parents": ["ef00bf203591c6ccc9b34c9f7fbfabfb843f804f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Chasen \u003cfchasen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2043020 - Part 2: Set IPP bandwidth.enabled pref from IPPUsageHelper and handle unlimited usage events  a=RyanVM\n\n- Moves the `bandwidth.enabled` pref setting out of `IPPFxaBaseAuthProvider` and into `IPPUsageHelper`\n- Adds an `UNLIMITED` usage state  in `IPPUsageHelper`.\n- Sets the pref from the entitlement's `limitedBandwidth` on IPPAuthProvider:StateChanged and from `usage.unlimited` on `UsageChanged`.\n- `IPProtectionPanel` event handler now clears bandwidth state for unlimited usage events.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303268\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304611\n", "files": ["browser/components/ipprotection/IPPUsageHelper.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/IPProtectionPanel.sys.mjs", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/browser/browser_IPPUsageHelper.js", "browser/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionPanel.js", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/docs/Preferences.rst", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/fxa/IPPFxaBaseAuthProvider.sys.mjs", "toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProtectionService.js"], "git_node": "f81caa4a93c723b8af3dda867c92bc44ebf43317", "git_parents": ["61db97a6d6bcd82aa210f8f865838f6d2d7aad88"], "node": "562799011ce32c850f3bd7fd2156b3313800fc3e", "parents": ["3f96763e07e336cff841f48f69e9b98b0614f95e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780540937, "git_changesets": ["c020b0cc739c2ab17790bf377b78e557b39f4f06", "e125f5631e0cfb8af402d13c5bc5007ca5de7a8a", "16243646bb08ab11a404ac58a4cad358107c489a", "614c6611898ab000478fed9ba40836cf1d783dce", "e95cf403c16884d92f1decdeb65b6bbc342c7b8c", "61db97a6d6bcd82aa210f8f865838f6d2d7aad88", "f81caa4a93c723b8af3dda867c92bc44ebf43317"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26721": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jed Davis \u003cjld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040477.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302076\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304623\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerRealpath.cpp"], "git_node": "f9fa60bab2c6230fa10fa5baedc7106443270f98", "git_parents": ["f81caa4a93c723b8af3dda867c92bc44ebf43317"], "node": "0edde7f72fa90265a0596633c967a2f24af11be3", "parents": ["562799011ce32c850f3bd7fd2156b3313800fc3e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780541216, "git_changesets": ["f9fa60bab2c6230fa10fa5baedc7106443270f98"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26722": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jed Davis \u003cjld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040515 - Rip out the symlink brokering.  a=RyanVM\n\nThis is almost certainly unused.  Bug 1380701 comment #23 mentioned\nPulseAudio in content processes, which is no longer supported.  (If\nyou flip `media.cubeb.sandbox` for testing, you'll need to turn off\nsandboxing; you should not flip that pref for production use.)\n\nIn general there are very few places left where sandboxed processes can\ncreate files, and none of them should need symlinks.  However, there\nmight be libraries which were calling symlink and silently failing.\n\nGiven all of that, this patch does not return symlink/symlinkat to being\nunexpected syscalls (crash on Nightly, ENOSYS otherwise) but instead just\nmakes them quietly fail with EPERM.  (This happens to match macOS, it's a\nreasonable error code, and tests can distinguish it from the EACCES of a\nbroker rejection.)\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301463\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304637\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/common/test/SandboxTestingChildTests.h", "security/sandbox/linux/SandboxBrokerClient.cpp", "security/sandbox/linux/SandboxBrokerClient.h", "security/sandbox/linux/SandboxFilter.cpp", "security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBroker.cpp", "security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerCommon.cpp", "security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerCommon.h", "security/sandbox/linux/gtest/TestBroker.cpp", "security/sandbox/test/browser_content_sandbox_fs_tests.js"], "git_node": "4571eace6574d6b3596b215d41ff9eb30f5ef4c8", "git_parents": ["f9fa60bab2c6230fa10fa5baedc7106443270f98"], "node": "dc27f8ae58cece6d66077fee72f738af82266dc9", "parents": ["0edde7f72fa90265a0596633c967a2f24af11be3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jed Davis \u003cjld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2040177.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302075\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304638\n", "files": ["security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBroker.cpp", "security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerCommon.h"], "git_node": "cea70c59f53ca9514987ab6ff46b88c1675be304", "git_parents": ["4571eace6574d6b3596b215d41ff9eb30f5ef4c8"], "node": "3a1656e81cfcb138ae63fefe3854924c4f0ee823", "parents": ["dc27f8ae58cece6d66077fee72f738af82266dc9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780541245, "git_changesets": ["4571eace6574d6b3596b215d41ff9eb30f5ef4c8", "cea70c59f53ca9514987ab6ff46b88c1675be304"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26723": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003crvandermeulen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2043020 - Fix test_IPPProxyManager_unlimited_usage on beta. a=bustage\n\nBeta's xpcshell head.js still uses the sinon-based setupStubs(sandbox, aOptions)\nsignature, so the uplifted test must create and pass a sandbox rather than calling\nsetupStubs with an options object directly.\n", "files": ["toolkit/components/ipprotection/tests/xpcshell/test_IPProxyManager.js"], "git_node": "26fa4bc042dfae8aa5a03e88405040243fa8f2af", "git_parents": ["cea70c59f53ca9514987ab6ff46b88c1675be304"], "node": "d912bbb5440df1eff553592fab242522b69a20d3", "parents": ["3a1656e81cfcb138ae63fefe3854924c4f0ee823"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780547302, "git_changesets": ["26fa4bc042dfae8aa5a03e88405040243fa8f2af"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26724": {"changesets": [{"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2042603 - Make urlbar sports suggestions status text the selected-text color when the row is selected.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302934\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304649\n", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/urlbar/view-nova.css", "browser/themes/shared/urlbar/view-proton.css"], "git_node": "3eaab15270cc8515ebbe680d747bee658419f567", "git_parents": ["26fa4bc042dfae8aa5a03e88405040243fa8f2af"], "node": "1105e2e2902be93b8bc283b57a801f3241267faf", "parents": ["d912bbb5440df1eff553592fab242522b69a20d3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780547635, "git_changesets": ["3eaab15270cc8515ebbe680d747bee658419f567"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26725": {"changesets": [{"author": "Release Engineering Landoscript \u003crelease+landoscript@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=