n \u003cjsudiaman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2033520 - Avoid the \"target-seeking\" logic when handling dragstart in the tabstrip.  a=RyanVM\n\nThis logic is necessary to handle links being dragged within Split View wrappers, but it should *not* be used for the purpose of calculating which element was initially dragged. This created a problem where \"dragging\" a scroll button would bring the tab underneath along with it.\n\nThis also slightly reworks the fix for Bug 2015708 (where both the Split View tabs and the main window can be dragged at the same time), as the root cause is similar. Tests added to verify both fixes.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303337\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304751\n", "files": ["browser/components/tabbrowser/content/drag-and-drop.js", "browser/components/tabbrowser/test/browser/dragdrop/browser.toml", "browser/components/tabbrowser/test/browser/dragdrop/browser_drag_horizontal_overflow.js", "browser/components/tabbrowser/test/browser/dragdrop/browser_drag_splitview.js"], "git_node": "9eb9253d4bf4ade80c15a28014893601ea88ed28", "git_parents": ["0e36b8476b7e898af2ad80b0d581061c1545db1d"], "node": "02beed00533974f425d04dd20c2ff2925a9ae24c", "parents": ["0678bc8d5f45cd8147bd5091dbe4d796e1d59c9c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780586741, "git_changesets": ["9eb9253d4bf4ade80c15a28014893601ea88ed28"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26734": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2038133 - [devtools] Consistently show filepicker on first save action from StyleEditor  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D301527\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304781\n", "files": ["devtools/client/styleeditor/StyleSheetEditor.sys.mjs", "devtools/client/styleeditor/test/browser_styleeditor_filesave.js", "devtools/client/styleeditor/test/browser_styleeditor_sourcemap_watching.js"], "git_node": "82e40c5afd0e546615c18918726a548128ff40a5", "git_parents": ["9eb9253d4bf4ade80c15a28014893601ea88ed28"], "node": "3d9bf855872db1d52450b65928ea900f9988ed14", "parents": ["02beed00533974f425d04dd20c2ff2925a9ae24c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780586767, "git_changesets": ["82e40c5afd0e546615c18918726a548128ff40a5"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26735": {"changesets": [{"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Update import-irregexp.py to exclude more V8 headers  a=RyanVM\n\nWe already excluded all v8 headers under `src`. Now we also exclude things like `#include \"include/v8config.h\"`.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302844\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304758\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/import-irregexp.py"], "git_node": "0a9ec73792d387cf7a827aaee6fba9b1bba3ccbc", "git_parents": ["82e40c5afd0e546615c18918726a548128ff40a5"], "node": "340130274077b671c1d8567f0c29f8c39b98639d", "parents": ["3d9bf855872db1d52450b65928ea900f9988ed14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Update irregexp to e88e94638bf0e99430828b1b27251b7e2db15147  a=RyanVM\n\nNon-trivial changes:\n- A bug fix involving overflow with large eats_at_least values: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7734956\n- A bug fix involving silent truncation of bitfields: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7806147\n- A bug fix involving reading too far backwards: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7766690\n- A fix for a bug that depended on multiple peephole passes: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7837558\n- A fix for a correctness issue involving regexp modifiers: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7826630\n- A change to use a single pass of peephole optimization instead of two, to decrease compile time\n- A couple fixes to eliminate over-eager unbound label assertions when compilation fails (fixes our bug 2042747)\n- A new optimization that allows fast rejection of certain inputs without ever entering the engine (I've opened bug 2042915)\n- A reentrancy bug that doesn't affect us because of different approaches to handling interrupts\n- Changes to simplify handling of overly large regexps\n- Developer-facing code to trace regexp execution\n- Changes to how V8 represents capture names in code we don't use\n- Changes to the precise boundaries of trusted vs untrusted sandbox code (irrelevant since we don't have a sandbox)\n- Optimizations in bytecode analysis (which is still disabled by default)\n- Changes to avoid redundant hashmap lookups\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302845\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304759\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-ast.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-analysis.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-analysis.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-generator.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-generator.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-peephole.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecodes-inl.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecodes.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-code-generator.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-compiler.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-compiler.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-graph-printer.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-interpreter.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler-tracer.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler-tracer.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-parser.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-stack.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-stack.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp.h", "js/src/irregexp/moz.yaml"], "git_node": "5678c9d631196619c98b926789cc493f4b75833c", "git_parents": ["0a9ec73792d387cf7a827aaee6fba9b1bba3ccbc"], "node": "b4ef48d0003eddc430c1bf49bd65b2ef79e3e3b5", "parents": ["340130274077b671c1d8567f0c29f8c39b98639d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Add existing patch to moz.yaml  a=RyanVM\n\nWhen I added this patch in bug 2032106, I forgot to add it to moz.yaml to be applied in the future.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302846\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304760\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/moz.yaml"], "git_node": "29b7ec42b70576f3052baa376bf513a861c7237e", "git_parents": ["5678c9d631196619c98b926789cc493f4b75833c"], "node": "3832162da1304791ddd82e0621dbf29a3b85802c", "parents": ["b4ef48d0003eddc430c1bf49bd65b2ef79e3e3b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Update patch disabling regexp bytecode analysis  a=RyanVM\n\nThe code this patch removed was changed. While updating, I rewrote the patch to #ifdef out the offending code instead of removing it, in the hopes that it will make it slightly more likely to apply cleanly in the future.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302847\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304761\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/patches/disable-bytecode-analysis.patch"], "git_node": "ad4baab4dc7190e2c5d96fc95031faf827f280f6", "git_parents": ["29b7ec42b70576f3052baa376bf513a861c7237e"], "node": "9d7750cc19a4727936726827441fe77a44e53b97", "parents": ["3832162da1304791ddd82e0621dbf29a3b85802c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Apply mozilla patches for irregexp  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302848\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304762\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-generator.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecode-peephole.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecodes-inl.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-code-generator.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-graph-printer.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-interpreter.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler-tracer.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler-tracer.h", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-macro-assembler.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-parser.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-stack.cc", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-stack.h"], "git_node": "d38afdc0b179a9e82c11e416510034a60729bf71", "git_parents": ["ad4baab4dc7190e2c5d96fc95031faf827f280f6"], "node": "79be7dee822b804d25f83591da20a03fb6dce049", "parents": ["9d7750cc19a4727936726827441fe77a44e53b97"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Add BitField shim  a=RyanVM\n\nThis is taken directly from v8/src/base/bit-field.h. The only changes are to convert DCHECK/CHECK into MOZ_ASSERT/MOZ_RELEASE_ASSERT.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302849\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304763\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/RegExpShim.h", "js/src/irregexp/import-irregexp.py", "js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-compiler.h", "js/src/irregexp/util/BitFieldShim.h"], "git_node": "c3437873582ed546d4424d5cff48438caf1db36a", "git_parents": ["d38afdc0b179a9e82c11e416510034a60729bf71"], "node": "cc3c0155c4912d204656a955829383d7ae26896c", "parents": ["79be7dee822b804d25f83591da20a03fb6dce049"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Simplify size limits  a=RyanVM\n\nV8 simplified some old vestigial code in https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7743527 and https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7743527. This is the equivalent on our end.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302850\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304764\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/RegExpAPI.cpp"], "git_node": "642b9085d2dfb85f8ae9e2d78fb8a2fc15012031", "git_parents": ["c3437873582ed546d4424d5cff48438caf1db36a"], "node": "b986460362a81b149b1cf6bc74fe65b650d03c6e", "parents": ["cc3c0155c4912d204656a955829383d7ae26896c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Add CheckedNumeric shim  a=RyanVM\n\nThis is a thin wrapper around our existing CheckedInt code.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302851\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304765\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/RegExpShim.h"], "git_node": "6221682c3827cc29c0c570c438d548ef26b1e3c9", "git_parents": ["642b9085d2dfb85f8ae9e2d78fb8a2fc15012031"], "node": "9096776592a161ead01443ef93d540c9c5f5db57", "parents": ["b986460362a81b149b1cf6bc74fe65b650d03c6e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Increase visibility of Operand  a=RyanVM\n\nOur minimum supported version of g++ is version 10, which does not support `using enum`. To work around this, `remove-using-enum.patch` rewrites one instance to use a non-class enum, and removes another entirely. However, in the latest irregexp update, code in regexp-peephole.cc actually makes use of the removed `using enum`. We need the enum defined in BytecodeOperandNames\u003cBytecode::Foo\u003e to be visible via BytecodeOperands\u003cBytecode::Foo\u003e. Claude suggested making `BytecodeOperandsBase\u003cbc\u003e` a subclass of `BytecodeOperandNames\u003cbc\u003e`, which (shockingly) works. It's gross, but hopefully we will eventually be able to remove this patch entirely once we move up to g++ version 11.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302852\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304766\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/imported/regexp-bytecodes-inl.h", "js/src/irregexp/patches/remove-using-enum.patch"], "git_node": "02a28e9a2c36c460cfa797467ee80ba5d4f73554", "git_parents": ["6221682c3827cc29c0c570c438d548ef26b1e3c9"], "node": "6ededeb018216f8d4012a91de504d3ec2bab67d8", "parents": ["9096776592a161ead01443ef93d540c9c5f5db57"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Iain Ireland \u003ciireland@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2041569: Miscellaneous shim update  a=RyanVM\n\nIn V8, this is `[[clang::lifetimebound]]` upstream when supported, which can be used for static analysis. It's not useful for us.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D302853\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304767\n", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/RegExpShim.h"], "git_node": "3dfa6f43a4f9337f9f0552c0eaa394d399a5ce2b", "git_parents": ["02a28e9a2c36c460cfa797467ee80ba5d4f73554"], "node": "76119fa0ffeb45863cef8aca8b25381cbc719400", "parents": ["6ededeb018216f8d4012a91de504d3ec2bab67d8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780587131, "git_changesets": ["0a9ec73792d387cf7a827aaee6fba9b1bba3ccbc", "5678c9d631196619c98b926789cc493f4b75833c", "29b7ec42b70576f3052baa376bf513a861c7237e", "ad4baab4dc7190e2c5d96fc95031faf827f280f6", "d38afdc0b179a9e82c11e416510034a60729bf71", "c3437873582ed546d4424d5cff48438caf1db36a", "642b9085d2dfb85f8ae9e2d78fb8a2fc15012031", "6221682c3827cc29c0c570c438d548ef26b1e3c9", "02a28e9a2c36c460cfa797467ee80ba5d4f73554", "3dfa6f43a4f9337f9f0552c0eaa394d399a5ce2b"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26736": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003crvandermeulen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Revert \"Bug 790194 - Changed all instances in dom/media/webrtc to std::from_chars r=bwc\" for causing bug 2044894.\n\nThis reverts commit 61c84c2e3eb27965efb3987bfc0f011500dd2697.\n", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/sdp/SdpHelper.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/sdp/SipccSdp.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/transport/test/turn_unittest.cpp"], "git_node": "3c04760be8163ce54b4cdf19c86aae02a7d9a707", "git_parents": ["3dfa6f43a4f9337f9f0552c0eaa394d399a5ce2b"], "node": "720d007a4b0a1c16f81c0a30263d218a07ac0e11", "parents": ["76119fa0ffeb45863cef8aca8b25381cbc719400"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780600238, "git_changesets": ["3c04760be8163ce54b4cdf19c86aae02a7d9a707"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26737": {"changesets": [{"author": "Zoya \u003czfatima@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032753 - updated SettingsSectionHeader params to include color and added tertiary color to AIFeatureHeader  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D300842\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304831\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/compose/settings/SettingsSectionHeader.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/settings/ai/AIControlsScreen.kt"], "git_node": "75f5051b48c3c51deef8ba652c1e4b7f3762c636", "git_parents": ["3c04760be8163ce54b4cdf19c86aae02a7d9a707"], "node": "9f28307dfde9c58c6711b1a09ac494608c5f6b06", "parents": ["720d007a4b0a1c16f81c0a30263d218a07ac0e11"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780600899, "git_changesets": ["75f5051b48c3c51deef8ba652c1e4b7f3762c636"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26738": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julie De Lorenzo \u003cjdelorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2037161:  Adds thumbnail border to TabGroupRow, extracts logic to shared component  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303415\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304838\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabgroups/TabGroupRow.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/ui/tabitems/SharedTabItemUi.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/ui/tabitems/TabListTabItem.kt"], "git_node": "6f1a0eb361f66206394c20d9321496aca11d90ac", "git_parents": ["75f5051b48c3c51deef8ba652c1e4b7f3762c636"], "node": "79426890a72af9dcec208d95a22ba4c8eed6abde", "parents": ["9f28307dfde9c58c6711b1a09ac494608c5f6b06"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780604046, "git_changesets": ["6f1a0eb361f66206394c20d9321496aca11d90ac"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26739": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julie De Lorenzo \u003cjdelorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2044751:  Fix offset calculation issue caused by header items in tabs tray  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304569\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304844\n", "files": ["mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/browser/compose/interactable/InteractableGrid.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/browser/compose/interactable/InteractableList.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/ui/tabpage/TabLayout.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/test/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/browser/compose/InteractableGridTest.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/test/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/browser/compose/InteractableListTest.kt"], "git_node": "cd8747810ddf5b0a3acbee1553e2c373d781a4fd", "git_parents": ["6f1a0eb361f66206394c20d9321496aca11d90ac"], "node": "5bfba75419d801bea6a6761ec1970dfd0eacc429", "parents": ["79426890a72af9dcec208d95a22ba4c8eed6abde"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780604132, "git_changesets": ["cd8747810ddf5b0a3acbee1553e2c373d781a4fd"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26740": {"changesets": [{"author": "Noah Bond \u003cnbond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2039600 - Do not display the tab UI until the tab data is fully loaded from disk  a=RyanVM\n\nUntil we can provide correct tab data at first-render, we should prevent the Tab Manager from rendering an incorrect initial state.\n\nOriginal Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303505\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304835\n", "files": ["mobile/android/android-components/components/ui/tabcounter/build.gradle", "mobile/android/android-components/components/ui/tabcounter/src/main/java/mozilla/components/ui/tabcounter/TabCounter.kt", "mobile/android/android-components/components/ui/tabcounter/src/test/AndroidManifest.xml", "mobile/android/android-components/components/ui/tabcounter/src/test/java/mozilla/components/ui/tabcounter/TabCounterComposableTest.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/redux/middleware/TabStorageMiddleware.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/redux/reducer/TabsTrayReducer.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/redux/state/TabsTrayState.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/ui/banner/TabsTrayBanner.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/main/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/ui/tabstray/TabsTray.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/test/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/redux/middleware/TabStorageMiddlewareTest.kt", "mobile/android/fenix/app/src/test/java/org/mozilla/fenix/tabstray/redux/reducer/TabsTrayStoreReducerTest.kt"], "git_node": "cfcf003a98e1beee2f6f93ae7ef2abdaba1283e4", "git_parents": ["cd8747810ddf5b0a3acbee1553e2c373d781a4fd"], "node": "c94aafe70b31dfa1afe6cd5fbf8e3029601f4126", "parents": ["5bfba75419d801bea6a6761ec1970dfd0eacc429"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780604221, "git_changesets": ["cfcf003a98e1beee2f6f93ae7ef2abdaba1283e4"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26741": {"changesets": [{"author": "Noah Bond \u003cnbond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "de