Claude was used to generate a test case for this.\n\nHopefully the extra check doesn't affect performance too much.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303400\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305440\n", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/gc/bug-2042465.js", "js/src/jit/CodeGenerator.cpp", "js/src/jit/MacroAssembler.cpp", "js/src/jit/MacroAssembler.h", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp"], "git_node": "387fb16ba99be52530b5204a10055efaa34135cc", "git_parents": ["0aff3327feb133e18b6ef5041e3d8ce446a52c85"], "node": "fe8f75175619d64b9b26f49a9090e795c57fb951", "parents": ["945aedee5adc7d8aa16bb0a55317efee0095dc8f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780971829, "git_changesets": ["387fb16ba99be52530b5204a10055efaa34135cc"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26802": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 2032185 - Update Widevine fallback downloader URLs for 4.10.3050.0.  a=RyanVM DONTBUILD\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D304106\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305441\n", "files": ["toolkit/content/gmp-sources/widevinecdm.json"], "git_node": "349f9bf744e6fc789037bb2dbb4f79486d967e79", "git_parents": ["387fb16ba99be52530b5204a10055efaa34135cc"], "node": "0b48d2c16278be0769949784b731eb928b33dc60", "parents": ["fe8f75175619d64b9b26f49a9090e795c57fb951"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780971860, "git_changesets": ["349f9bf744e6fc789037bb2dbb4f79486d967e79"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26803": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1936955 - Refactor ExpirationTrackerImpl to only allow StaticMutex or PlaceholderLock.  a=RyanVM\n\nThis patch makes it so that ExpirationTrackerObserver now holds the\nlock when issuing its callbacks to ensure the owner hasn't been\ndestroyed yet during shutdown races. PlaceholderLock does nothing,\nso it is always safe to use, even if it has already been freed. The\nStaticMutex is also always safe to use, because its lifetime now\nexceeds that of ExpirationTrackerImpl and ExpirationTrackerObserver.\n\nIt also moves the timer callbacks into ExpirationTrackerObserver via\nnsITimerCallback, as it can suffer from the same shutdown race as\nthe memory-pressure events.\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D303950\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305442\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/SharedSurfacesParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/SharedSurfacesParent.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxFont.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxFont.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxGradientCache.cpp", "image/SurfaceCache.cpp", "xpcom/ds/nsExpirationTracker.h"], "git_node": "1c47c3267b7a3f726aadc3e8ed05222300b784e4", "git_parents": ["349f9bf744e6fc789037bb2dbb4f79486d967e79"], "node": "5cee398d0b41d3275f35e72c8ca0cf3163287fbe", "parents": ["0b48d2c16278be0769949784b731eb928b33dc60"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780971919, "git_changesets": ["1c47c3267b7a3f726aadc3e8ed05222300b784e4"], "user": "rvandermeulen@mozilla.com"}, "26804": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jonathan Moss \u003cjmoss@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1944610 - Read Windows cache paths from worker environment.  a=RyanVM\n\nOriginal Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D261470\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D305399\n", "files": ["taskcluster/gecko_taskgraph/transforms/job/common.py", "taskcluster/scripts/run-task", "testing/mozharness/configs/builds/taskcluster_base_windows.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/talos/windows_taskcluster_config.py"], "git_node": "561d873535e91ef8c8e934d0e8d74e691014fe1f", "git_parents": ["1c47c3267b7a3f726aadc3e8ed05222300b784e4"], "node": "e0384af2187c474e323b74a04f02093daf16ac55", "parents": ["5cee398d0b41d3275f35e72c8ca0cf3163287fbe"], "tags": []}], "date": 1780971967, "git_changesets": ["561d873535e91ef8c8e934